            <title>[FLUME-1981] Rpc client expiration can be done in a more thread-safe way</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-1981</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the destroyConnection() call happens just before a client.append() or client.getBatchSize(), it is possible that an EventDeliveryException is thrown which is caused by an NPE (since destroyConnection() will set client to null). &lt;/p&gt;</description>
